1) checkout the source
svn checkout http://svn.instinctualsoftware.com/informer/trunk --username=yourname

2) cd to the source
cd trunk

3) edit conf/instinctual.conf line 3 (set to your hostname/IP address):
server: 127.0.0.1

4) edit lib/instinctual/settings.py line 24:
DATABASE_ENGINE = 'sqlite3'

5) run the dev server
./bin/runserver

6) it will prompt you with a series of questions...

You just installed Django's auth system, which means you don't have any superusers defined.
Would you like to create one now? (yes/no):
---> ENTER yes

Username (Leave blank to use 'yourname'): 
---> ENTER informer

E-mail address: 
---> ENTER (anything you want)

Password: 
---> ENTER informer

Password (again): 
---> ENTER informer

7) The server should now be running... make sure you the following with your IP from step 3:

Django version 0.96, using settings 'instinctual.settings'
Development server is running at http://127.0.0.1:8000/
Quit the server with CONTROL-C.

8) Set up a fake project

http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/informer/project/add/

Name: nike
Description: fake project

(click save)

9) Set up a fake shot

http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/informer/shot/add/

Project: nike: fake project
Shot: sweatshop
Description: children making shoes
Status: in progress
Handles: 0
Frames: 200

10) Browse to the projects page

http://127.0.0.1:8000/informer/1.0/html/projects/

11) select nike
12) select sweatshop
